claim.claim-text:
1. A solid-state laser apparatus comprising:
a master oscillator configured to output laser light having at least one longitudinal mode, the master oscillator being capable of changing the spectral linewidth of the laser light output therefrom;
at least one amplifier located downstream of the master oscillator on an optical path;
a wavelength converter located downstream of the amplifier on the optical path;
a detector configured to detect a spectrum of the laser light; and
a controller configured to control the spectral linewidth of the laser light output from the master oscillator based on a detection result of the detector.
